Operating System Security :
                          The way of secure OS from unauthorized access
                          is called OS security . It include window and
                          Linux both.

 Main part of Security:
                       * Accounts :
                                    Which number of user in OS , Admin , guest
                                    , normal user . we should close the guest
                                    password . close direct login from root m,
                                    every user should have unique password.
                       * Passwords :
                                    Login password  . We should use strong
                                    password more than 12 character
                       * File Permission :
                                         Which file has which permission.
                                         Like read, write , or execute.
                                         Hacker first find chmod 777 file.
                                         To remain safe  keep important
                                         files in chmod 700 only owner access

                       * Logging and auditing :
                                                It is like OS CCTV , hacker often
                                                delete it so no one can know about
                                                his logging.
                                                To save from it Logging keep on in
                                                /var/log/auth.log
                       * Patching and Update :
                                            In old version there are holes where
                                            attacker attack . So we should regularly
                                            update apt and upgrade every week

                       * Firewalls :
                                    It is like the gatekeeper which stop unauthorized
                                    entry in window or linux . So we should on it and we
                                    should close the non important ports

   Points Of conclusion :-
                          Where attacker can attack easily :
                                                            Weak account + Week password
                                                            + open permission + old version.

                          To keep safe :
                                        Strong account + Strong password + tight permission
                                        + Update OS + Firewall + Log